import{o as s,c as n,j as t,n as i,e as r,ae as l,p as h}from"./chunks/framework.BSk3HXt1.js";const c={class:"language-toggle-wrapper"},p={class:"language-toggle-bar"},d={class:"bilingual-title"},u={key:0,class:"zh-text"},g={key:1,class:"en-text"},b=JSON.parse('{"title":"科技狂潮 vs 石油危機：亞洲經濟新現實為全球敲響警鐘 | Tech boom vs oil crisis: Asia’s new economic reality is a warning for the world","description":"","frontmatter":{"outline":[2,3],"title":"科技狂潮 vs 石油危機：亞洲經濟新現實為全球敲響警鐘 | Tech boom vs oil crisis: Asia’s new economic reality is a warning for the world"},"headers":[],"relativePath":"news/tech-boom-oil-crisis-asia-economy-warning.md","filePath":"news/tech-boom-oil-crisis-asia-economy-warning.md"}'),m={name:"news/tech-boom-oil-crisis-asia-economy-warning.md"},w=Object.assign(m,{setup(v){const e=h("bilingual");return(f,a)=>(s(),n("div",null,[t("div",c,[t("div",p,[t("button",{class:i(["language-toggle-btn",{active:e.value==="bilingual"}]),onClick:a[0]||(a[0]=o=>e.value="bilingual")},"中英雙語",2),t("button",{class:i(["language-toggle-btn",{active:e.value==="zh"}]),onClick:a[1]||(a[1]=o=>e.value="zh")},"純中文",2),t("button",{class:i(["language-toggle-btn",{active:e.value==="en"}]),onClick:a[2]||(a[2]=o=>e.value="en")},"純英文",2)])]),t("div",{class:i("bilingual-article mode-"+e.value)},[t("h1",d,[e.value!=="en"?(s(),n("span",u,"科技狂潮 vs 石油危機：亞洲經濟新現實為全球敲響警鐘")):r("",!0),e.value!=="zh"?(s(),n("span",g,"Tech boom vs oil crisis: Asia’s new economic reality is a warning for the world")):r("",!0)]),a[3]||(a[3]=l('<div style="text-align:center;margin:24px 0 32px 0;"><img src="/ai-news/tech-boom-oil-crisis-asia-economy-warning/hero.png" alt="Tech boom vs oil crisis in Asia" style="border-radius:16px;max-width:100%;box-shadow:0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.15);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);"></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">在南韓，全球能源供應危機的衝擊感受至深。政府官員不得不呼籲全民節約能源、調降經濟成長預測，並警告高通膨與韓元匯率跌至 17 年新低所帶來的衝擊。然而，南韓最大規模的企業卻在此時大賺破紀錄利潤，其股市甚至創下歷史新高。</p><p class="en-text">In South Korea, a global energy supply crunch has hit hard. Officials have advised energy conservation, cut growth forecasts and warned of fallout from high inflation and 17-year lows in the value of its currency. Yet the nation’s largest companies are raking in record profits, and its stock market is hitting all-time highs.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">這種矛盾的現象凸顯出，亞洲目前正同時並存著兩種截然不同的經濟現實。</p><p class="en-text">The contradiction underscores how, in Asia, there are now two economic realities.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">伊朗戰爭引發的歷史性石油衝擊，正加速該地區經濟命運的分化。其中一方是由科技巨擘與人工智慧（AI）的宏偉前景所驅動；另一方則籠罩在燃料短缺與物價飆升的陰霾中，甚至面臨人道危機的威脅。</p><p class="en-text">The historic oil shock caused by the war in Iran is accelerating a divergence of economic fortunes across the region. One is driven by tech giants and the promises of artificial intelligence. The other is darkened by fuel scarcity and rising prices that threaten a humanitarian crisis.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">隨著石油短缺在亞洲造成的非對稱衝擊不斷拉大這道鴻溝，經濟學家警告，此一現象將對整個亞洲大陸——以及世界其他依賴亞洲貿易的地區——的貨幣政策、政治穩定和未來經濟成長產生重大影響。</p><p class="en-text">As the disproportionate impact of oil shortages in Asia widens the divide, economists warn that the phenomenon has significant ramifications for monetary policy, political stability, and future economic growth across the continent – and other parts of the world that rely on it for trade.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">美林證券（Bank of America Merrill Lynch）南韓與中國經濟學家 Benson Wu 表示：「沒錯，經濟正蓬勃發展，股市表現非常亮眼，但我們幾乎看不到財富效應外溢到該地區的日常實體經濟活動中。我認為這正是讓許多觀察家感到非常不安的地方。」</p><p class="en-text">“Yes, the economy is booming, the equity market is doing very well, but we see limited wealth effect spilling over to the daily activities happening in the region,” said Benson Wu, a Korea and China economist at Bank of America Merrill Lynch. “I think that is something really troubling many observers.”</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">這種落差顯示出日益加劇的貧富差距。這種不平等最初因新冠疫情而加劇，如今又受到中東衝突的火上澆油。過去兩個月來，原本承載全球五分之一原油運輸的霍爾木茲海峽（Strait of Hormuz）航運已幾近中斷，導致國際油價狂飆至四年新高。</p><p class="en-text">The disparity is indicative of growing inequality, exacerbated first by the Covid-19 pandemic, and now the conflict in the Middle East. Shipping via the Strait of Hormuz, through which one-fifth of the world’s crude oil normally flows, has dried up over the past two months, sending oil prices to four-year highs.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">高度仰賴中東能源進口的亞洲，承受了這波油價暴漲的首當其衝衝擊。但影響並非均等分佈。日本、南韓和台灣等位於東亞的高科技先進經濟體，擁有更充裕的燃料儲備可供調配，並擁有雄厚的資金來支付更高昂的價格以確保能源供應安全。</p><p class="en-text">Asia, which is heavily reliant on the Middle East for energy, has borne the initial brunt of those higher prices. But the impact isn’t spread evenly. Advanced, tech-heavy economies in East Asia like Japan, South Korea and Taiwan have bigger fuel reserves to draw on, as well as the cash to pay higher prices to secure more stocks.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">相較之下，印度、菲律賓和泰國等以傳統製造業和服務業為經濟主導的國家，則在獲取燃料和減緩經濟活動放緩方面陷入了更艱難的掙扎。</p><p class="en-text">Meanwhile, nations like India, the Philippines and Thailand, whose growth is dominated by traditional manufacturing and services, are facing greater struggles to secure fuel and offset slowing economic activity.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">Wu 指出：「這些地區第一沒有享受到當前 AI 或科技浪潮帶來的太多紅利；第二，它們卻可能承受著更多來自中東衝突引發的通膨壓力衝擊。這是我們必須非常密切關注的事。」</p><p class="en-text">“These are regions that, number one, they are not sharing that much of the good things coming from the current AI or tech story. And number two, they are potentially experiencing more shock from the inflationary pressures coming from the Middle East conflict,” said Wu. “That is something we need to watch very closely.”</p></div><hr><h2 id="🤖-新石油的誕生-晶片霸權與-ai-狂潮-the-ai-engine-and-new-oil" tabindex="-1">🤖 新石油的誕生：晶片霸權與 AI 狂潮 (The AI Engine and &quot;New Oil&quot;) <a class="header-anchor" href="#🤖-新石油的誕生-晶片霸權與-ai-狂潮-the-ai-engine-and-new-oil" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;🤖 新石油的誕生：晶片霸權與 AI 狂潮 (The AI Engine and &quot;New Oil&quot;)&quot;">​</a></h2><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">半導體早已無所不在地驅動著從智慧型手機、汽車到家用電器的一切，這為該產業贏得了「新石油」的美譽。而現在，AI 狂潮更是讓半導體需求進入了超高速成長期。</p><p class="en-text">Semiconductors were already powering everything from smartphones to cars to home appliances, earning the industry a reputation as “the new oil.” Now the AI boom is turbocharging demand.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">聯合國貿易和發展會議（UNCTAD）的一份報告預估，全球 AI 市場規模到 2033 年將飆升至 4.8 兆美元，比 2023 年暴增 25 倍。摩根士丹利（Morgan Stanley）則估算，未來兩年內在 AI 基礎設施上的支出可能突破 3 兆美元。</p><p class="en-text">A UN Trade and Development report projected that the global AI market will grow to $4.8 trillion by 2033 — a 25-fold increase from 2023. Morgan Stanley estimated that spending on AI infrastructure could exceed $3 trillion in the next two years.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">這種強勁的經濟效應在世界半導體晶片製造的重鎮最為顯著。</p><p class="en-text">The economic effects are most apparent in the chipmaking capitals of the world.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">台灣第一季 GDP 成長率寫下 39 年來新高的 13.69%，其股票市場市值也超越加拿大，躍升為全球第六大股市。這些驚人漲幅主要歸功於半導體晶圓代工巨擘台積電（TSMC）——台積電一家企業的市值便佔了台灣證券交易所總市值的 40% 以上。</p><p class="en-text">Taiwan’s first-quarter GDP growth notched a 39-year high of 13.69%, as its equity market overtook Canada’s to become the world’s sixth-largest. The gains are largely attributable to the chip-making behemoth Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company (TSMC), which accounts for more than 40% of the Taiwan Stock Exchange.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">首爾股市在最近幾週也相繼超越倫敦和加拿大，成為全球第七大股市。南韓兩大企業巨頭——晶片大廠三星電子（Samsung Electronics）和 SK 海力士（SK Hynix）——在今年第一季均繳出創紀錄的利潤，三星的市值甚至已突破了 1 兆美元大關。</p><p class="en-text">Seoul’s stock market has also surpassed London’s and Canada’s to become the world’s seventh-largest in recent weeks. South Korea’s two biggest corporations, chipmakers Samsung Electronics and SK Hynix, have reported record profits in the first three months of this year, and Samsung’s market capitalization has risen above $1 trillion.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">AI 是一項高度消耗能源的技術，亞洲的大多數高科技中心都極度依賴進口燃料和原材料。然而，科技產業所湧入的龐大資金，大幅緩解了這些樞紐確保供應能力的擔憂。</p><p class="en-text">AI is energy-intensive, and most high-tech hubs in Asia need to import fuel and raw materials. However, the vast amount of money in the industry has eased concerns about their abilities to secure supplies.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">法國巴黎銀行（BNP Paribas）亞太區股票與衍生性商品策略主管 Jason Lui 表示：「半導體公司有能力將這些額外的能源成本轉嫁給終端客戶。半導體的供需關係極度失衡，因此手中有貨才是最重要的，這讓晶片商擁有了極為強大的定價權。」</p><p class="en-text">“Semiconductor companies will be able to pass on these additional costs to the end customers,” said Jason Lui, head of Asia-Pacific equity and derivative strategy at French bank BNP Paribas. “The supply demand for semiconductors is very skewed, so having the product is more important, and they have very strong pricing power.”</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">美商美銀亞太區科技研究協調主管 Simon Woo 表示，只要美國的大型科技巨頭持續對 AI 進行巨額投資，亞洲的晶片製造商和供應鏈就將保持榮景。他補充指出，由於這些科技股表現過於亮眼，投資人已不再滿足於傳統產業所能提供的平淡回報。</p><p class="en-text">Simon Woo, Asia-Pacific tech research coordinator at Bank of America, said as long as major US tech companies continue investing in AI, Asian chipmakers and suppliers should flourish as well. He added that as those stocks have overperformed, investors are no longer satisfied with the returns that traditional sectors may offer.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">他形容說：「當你審視與 AI 相關的公司時，如果你只預估 10% 或 20% 的成長，投資人會大喊：『我的天啊，這也太低了！』在 AI 時代，你至少得聽到 50% 甚至 100% 的爆發性成長。」</p><p class="en-text">“When you look at the AI-related companies, if you say 10% growth, 20% growth, investors say, ‘Oh my God, too low,’” he said. “In the AI era, at least you have to hear 50%, 100% growth.”</p></div><hr><h2 id="📉-警鐘長鳴-k-型經濟與潛在的社會危機-the-stark-reality-of-the-k-shaped-economy" tabindex="-1">📉 警鐘長鳴：K 型經濟與潛在的社會危機 (The Stark Reality of the &quot;K-Shaped&quot; Economy) <a class="header-anchor" href="#📉-警鐘長鳴-k-型經濟與潛在的社會危機-the-stark-reality-of-the-k-shaped-economy" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;📉 警鐘長鳴：K 型經濟與潛在的社會危機 (The Stark Reality of the &quot;K-Shaped&quot; Economy)&quot;">​</a></h2><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">然而，正當 AI 狂潮如火如荼進行的同時，亞洲最脆弱的底層人口正因中東戰火而面臨極其嚴峻的生存困境。</p><p class="en-text">While the AI frenzy continues, the most vulnerable populations in Asia face dire consequences from the war in the Middle East.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">聯合國開發計劃署（UNDP）預估，這場中東衝突已使亞太地區多達 880 萬人面臨陷入貧窮的危機，並可能拖累該區域的 GDP 成長率達 0.3% 至 0.8%。</p><p class="en-text">The United Nations Development Programme estimates that the war has put 8.8 million people in the Asia-Pacific region at risk of falling into poverty, and could curb regional GDP by 0.3% to 0.8%.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">這種極端的對比被稱為「K 型經濟（K-shaped economy）」。該詞彙指的是社會上層與下層階級之間差距急劇擴大的分化趨勢，在新冠疫情過後因弱勢群體承受不成比例的衝擊而廣為流傳。經濟學家指出，目前的伊朗局勢正在產生完全相同的效應。</p><p class="en-text">The stark contrast has become known as the “K-shaped economy.” The term refers to a steepening deviation between upper and lower economic classes, popularized after the Covid-19 pandemic disproportionately hit underprivileged groups. Economists said the war in Iran is having a similar effect.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">新加坡尤索夫伊薩東南亞研究院（ISEAS – Yusof Ishak Institute）客座高級研究員 Jayant Menon 指出：「在經濟下行期間，窮人總是承受最沉重的打擊，而在經濟復甦時，他們卻無法均等分享成果。這種不平等不斷累積，在某種程度上甚至會形成自我實現的惡性循環。」</p><p class="en-text">“The poor get hit harder during these downturns, and they don’t share equally in the upturn,” said Jayant Menon, a visiting senior fellow with the ISEAS – Yusof Ishak Institute in Singapore. “That inequality accumulates and in some ways, is self-fulfilling.”</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">這道鴻溝會拉大到何種程度，取決於各國政府的因應作為，以及美軍與伊朗軍隊對峙控制霍爾木茲海峽的時間長短。此外，如果晶圓製造與 AI 數據中心瘋狂擴建，進一步排擠並「吸乾」其他民生與產業領域的能源，那麼 AI 的蓬勃發展甚至可能加劇能源短缺的災情。</p><p class="en-text">How far the gap widens depends on government action, as well as how long the Strait of Hormuz remains occupied by US and Iranian military forces. The rush to build out AI may also aggravate the shortfall, if manufacturing and data centers siphon energy away from other sectors.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">即便是在那些從 AI 熱潮中獲益匪淺的經濟體內部，財富的分配也極其不均。在南韓，數以萬計的三星員工因對薪資成長滯後的不滿而威脅發起大罷工。隨著民間消費力道疲弱，南韓央行已發出警訊，指出民眾實體感受與官方亮眼的 GDP 數據之間存在著日漸嚴重的「脫節」。</p><p class="en-text">Even within economies that have benefited from the AI boom, the resulting riches have been unevenly spread. In South Korea, tens of thousands of Samsung workers are threatening to strike amid broader discontent over lagging pay. As consumer activity has weakened, the central bank has warned about the growing misalignment between real sentiment and headline GDP growth.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">中華經濟研究院（CIER）台灣東南亞國家協會研究中心主任徐遵慈（Kristy Hsu）指出，「K 型」經濟分化的現象在今年也引起了台灣政府官員的密切關注。</p><p class="en-text">The “K-shape” phenomenon has also caught the attention of Taiwanese officials this year, said Kristy Hsu, director of the Taiwan ASEAN Studies Center at the Chung-hua Institution for Economic Research.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">她表示，半導體產業僅佔台灣總就業人口的 4% 左右，但科技業基層員工的薪資可以是其他行業同儕的五倍之多。她警告說，若把過多的資源與關注度傾注在單一產業，可能會剝奪其他產業所需的電力等基礎資源，從而使問題更加雪上加霜。</p><p class="en-text">She said the semiconductor industry only accounts for about 4% of Taiwan’s workforce, but the salary for entry-level workers can be as much as five times that of their peers. Too much attention on one sector may also deprive others of resources like electricity, which would further exacerbate the issue, she added.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">她感嘆道：「對於一般大眾、尤其是 AI 半導體產業而言，人人都歌頌著美好的亮麗未來；但對於我們這些經濟學家和智庫學者來說，這絕對是台灣面臨的極其嚴重的隱憂與風險。」</p><p class="en-text">“For the general public and especially the AI semiconductor industry, they all talk about this bright future,” she said. “But for economists and think-tankers like us, we do consider this a very severe risk facing Taiwan.”</p></div><hr><h2 id="⚖️-貨幣政策的兩難-照顧-20-的繁榮-還是-80-的掙扎-the-monetary-dilemma-20-vs-80" tabindex="-1">⚖️ 貨幣政策的兩難：照顧 20% 的繁榮，還是 80% 的掙扎？ (The Monetary Dilemma: 20% vs. 80%) <a class="header-anchor" href="#⚖️-貨幣政策的兩難-照顧-20-的繁榮-還是-80-的掙扎-the-monetary-dilemma-20-vs-80" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;⚖️ 貨幣政策的兩難：照顧 20% 的繁榮，還是 80% 的掙扎？ (The Monetary Dilemma: 20% vs. 80%)&quot;">​</a></h2><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">AI 繁榮與能源危機的並存，為各國政府帶來了前所未有的挑戰，考驗著如何調和這日益斷裂的經濟體系。</p><p class="en-text">The combination of the AI boom and the energy crisis poses a unique challenge for governments on how to reconcile an increasingly fractured economy.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">不斷加深的所得分配不均，不僅大幅升高了社會動盪和政治動亂的風險，更會直接扼殺長期的經濟穩定。因為財富過度集中在少數人手中，會嚴重削弱推動整體經濟運轉的絕大多數一般民眾的消費力。</p><p class="en-text">Deepening income inequality not only heightens the risk of social and political unrest; it also threatens long-term economic stability, because a narrowing concentration of wealth erodes spending power among the majority population that drives economic activity.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">經濟學家指出，表面上平穩的經濟成長數據，往往掩蓋了底層早已盤根錯節、極易惡化加劇的深層結構性弊病。</p><p class="en-text">Economists said the perception of steady growth has masked underlying structural issues that can easily compound.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">徐遵慈直言：「這確實是一個嶄新的課題。台灣不可能承受失去台積電或這些高科技產業的代價，但不同群體、不同家庭和不同產業之間日益拉大的貧富差距，必須得到實質的解決。」</p><p class="en-text">“This is really a new issue,” said Hsu. “Taiwan cannot afford to not have TSMC or all this high tech, but this widening gap for different groups, different households and different sectors, needs to be addressed.”</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">與此同時，各國央行必須在提振經濟與對抗通膨之間取得極其微妙的平衡，而各國之間貨幣政策的各行其是，甚至可能在區域內引發更劇烈的不平等。</p><p class="en-text">Meanwhile, central banks must find a balance between boosting growth and combating inflation, while uneven monetary policy among countries could trigger greater regional inequality.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">匯豐銀行（HSBC）亞洲區首席經濟學家 Frederic Neumann 犀利地問道：「你究竟是要根據那高達 8% 的 GDP 成長率（因為單一科技業表現爆表）來調升利率？還是要為另外 80% 根本毫無成長、甚至在痛苦掙扎的實體經濟來制定貨幣政策？」</p><p class="en-text">“Do you set interest rates according to 8% GDP growth, because one sector is driving this? Or do you set monetary policy for the other 80% of the economy that is not growing?” said Frederic Neumann, chief Asia economist at HSBC.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">對單一產業的過度依賴，使得押寶高科技發展的經濟體在面臨市場回檔時顯得極其脆弱——一旦 AI 泡沫破裂或技術發展放緩，抑或是大宗商品短缺加劇最終妨礙了電子零組件的實體生產，衝擊將不堪設想。</p><p class="en-text">Overreliance on one industry makes economies betting on high-tech development vulnerable to market corrections, if AI development falters, or if worsening commodities shortages eventually hinder production of electronic components.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">然而，Neumann 警告說，不平等的持續擴大將帶來前所未有的全球性經濟衝擊。</p><p class="en-text">However, Neumann warned that a continued rise in inequality also would have unprecedented economic implications.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">Neumann 憂心地指出：「真正的風險在於，這種 K 型的經濟分化將永遠定型，雙方再也沒有交會與重新收斂的一天。」</p><p class="en-text">“The risk is that the K-shaped recovery will stay a K forever, that there is no reconvergence,” Neumann said.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">雖然這些影響目前在亞洲最為顯著，但 Neumann 警告，隨著製造業萎縮和消費者信心下降，這種衝擊很快就會外溢到其他依賴亞洲貿易的西方經濟體。</p><p class="en-text">While the ramifications are currently most evident in Asia, Neumann said that as manufacturing and consumer sentiment decline, that is likely to spill over into other economies that rely on the region for trade.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">美國作為全球最大的原油與天然氣生產國，雖然對燃料價格衝擊的免疫力較高，但其實目前也正經歷著非常相似的經濟雙重化現象。今年第一季，在 AI 領域的龐大投資強勢支撐了美國的 GDP 數據，但同時間美國的加油站汽油價格已攀升至四年新高，普通民眾的消費開支也明顯放緩。</p><p class="en-text">The US, which is more insulated from fuel price shocks as the world’s largest producer of crude oil and natural gas, is already experiencing a similar bifurcation. Investment in AI boosted growth in the first quarter, even as gas prices rose to four-year highs and consumer spending slowed.</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">Neumann 總結道：「亞洲所得分配不均惡化與 K 型分化的社會趨勢，最終必然會傳導並衝擊美國。這對美國而言，既是經濟成長的重創，也是通膨高企的催化劑，這意味著它也將進一步加劇並鎖定美國本土經濟的 K 型分化。」</p><p class="en-text">“These social trends of rising income inequality and the K-shaped recovery in Asia will ultimately transmit themselves to the US,” Neumann said. “It is both a hit to US growth and a hit to US inflation, and that means that it reinforces the K for the US economy as well.”</p></div><div class="bilingual-paragraph"><p class="zh-text">CNN 記者 John Liu 對本報導亦有貢獻。</p><p class="en-text">CNN’s John Liu contributed reporting.</p></div><div class="original-source-wrapper"><div class="source-label"><span class="zh-text">🌐 閱讀英文原文：</span><span class="en-text">🌐 Read Original Article:</span></div><a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2026/05/12/tech/tech-boom-oil-crisis-asia-economy-warning-intl-hnk-dst" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="source-link-btn"> CNN Business <span style="font-size:0.8rem;">↗</span></a></div>',48))],2)]))}});export{b as __pageData,w as default};
